  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "One could only see on the roof, because in Haifa, the roofs are flat, so people could stand.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And you saw people waving from very, very far, what you-- whatever you-- they eye can discern.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And then, an hour or two after we were in Haifa-- arrived in Haifa, they gave us pieces of leaflets, which I will like to show you, in which there were instructions, that everything that we have, that means the knapsacks that we have, should be left behind, and we should disembark.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And they put to our disposal three English ships, and they will take us further.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] We did not want to disembark.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "We were helped by the English batons to disembark.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were-- we were pushed [INAUDIBLE]",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Certain children they took and carried them down.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "When we came down, we were shown directly into-- straight behind the was a ship standing, an English ship.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we were shown up to go on that ship.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The name of the ship was called When we came in, what we thought-- what we saw was again that was a fully prepared ship for carrying [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Everything was taken out from inside, and again bunks putting up.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we were shown there, we get into a bunk.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The people of the-- we were, as I mentioned before, 4,500 on the And they divided it in the three ships, 1,400 in each and every ship.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "A few hours later, the ships started moving.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "To much to our disappointment, we couldn't explain it, we saw us moving away from the sun.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That-- that mean that we're we're going westward.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were supposed to go a bit westward for Cypress, because Cypress is westward from-- from Palestine.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
